parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or fail to shift gears, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The transmission shifts rough
fails to shift past a certain gear
the hold light flashes
the transmission makes loud noises
the transmission slips into gear unexpectedly
and the vehicle may jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission computer can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to premature wear, failure to shift gears, and unexpected movements, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission computer sends incorrect signals
causing the transmission to shift erratically
select incorrect gears
or fail to shift gears altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to lose awareness of their speed, which can lead to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer does not display the correct speed
or the speedometer is broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt retractor can prevent the seat belt from functioning properly, which can lead to a failure to restrain the occupant in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt alarm sounds continuously
the dashboard warning light remains illuminated
the seat belt fails to move forward when the door is opened
the seat belt moves back and forth while driving
the motorized belt stops working completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the brake line can cause a complete loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pedal
brake pedal goes all the way to the floor
popping sound when pressing the brake pedal
air hissing sound when pumping the brakes
complete loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden deployment of the airbag can cause injuries, including facial burns and neck pain, and can also lead to accidents due to the unexpected distraction.
symptoms: Airbag deploys unexpectedly
facial burns
neck pain
sudden and forceful application of the brakes.
